    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Silver coins of Spain and Spanish America introduced in the mid-14th century and issued until the mid-19th century, except in Guatemala where issue continued in copper-nickel into the 20th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Monedas de plata de España y de la América española, introducidas a mediados del siglo XIV y emitidas hasta mediados del siglo XIX, exceptuando Guatemala en donde su emisión continuó en cuproniquel hasta el siglo XX.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zilveren munten die in Spanje en Spaans-Amerika halverwege de 14e eeuw voor het eerst werden geslagen. De uitgifte werd stopgezet in de 19e eeuw behalve in Guatemala, waar de munt tot in de 20e eeuw werd gehandhaafd in een koper-nikkellegering.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>西班牙與拉丁美洲的銀幣，於十四世紀中葉推行，發行至十九世紀中葉，然而里爾幣於瓜地馬拉，繼續以銅鎳材質發行至二十世紀。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
